class="entry-text"><p>While the neat layout and pleasant, calming color scheme of the website make an agreeable first impression on me, the poor quality of the three hero images on the home page really stands out on a desktop screen, watering down the otherwise professional look of the site.</p><p>Beyond that, the desktop site is a breeze to navigate, with key pages, such as service descriptions, testimonials, booking information, and contact details, easy to find via the floating top menu. The desktop site also performed admirably on Google's PageSpeed Insights test, where it scored 99/100 for performance and 100/100 for best practices.</p></div></div><h4>Mobile Review</h4><div
class="entry-website-mobile"><div
data-src="https://www.zarla.com/images/zarla-websiteexample-physio-solutions-2024079-mobile.webp"
